at that rate?

02:39.160 --> 02:40.325
(door buzzes)

02:42.962 --> 02:43.996
(groans)

02:43.998 --> 02:45.030
(thud)

02:45.032 --> 02:46.532
What? (gasps)

02:48.701 --> 02:50.135
Hmm. No pulse.

02:50.137 --> 02:51.904
Oh, wait, that's me.

02:52.839 --> 02:54.940
Dead. So sad.

02:54.942 --> 02:57.009
He was a true friend.

02:57.011 --> 03:00.145
Mm-hmm. Excellent.

03:00.147 --> 03:02.381
(trumpet playing taps)

03:02.383 --> 03:05.984
I can't believe
dr. Nussbaum's dead.

03:05.986 --> 03:09.121
Um, we've had
a lot of therapists.

03:09.123 --> 03:10.556
Which one was he again?

03:10.558 --> 03:13.492
He was the one who
helped us communicate.

03:13.494 --> 03:14.860
You never listen
to a word I say!

03:14.862 --> 03:16.995
