15:39.606 --> 15:43.541
Saint francis himself
would vomit with rage!

15:43.543 --> 15:45.143
Okay, you heard him,
people.

15:45.145 --> 15:47.078
That was great,
just a little more energy.

15:47.080 --> 15:49.047
Sir, I know you're
getting frustrated,

15:49.049 --> 15:51.582
So we recorded some
future scenarios.

15:51.584 --> 15:54.886
Yes, let's see what life
will be like when I'm old.

15:54.888 --> 15:56.955
I'm going to build homes
for the homeless

15:56.957 --> 15:58.890
With my boyfriend sean,

15:58.892 --> 16:01.492
Then it's off to vassar
in the fall.

16:01.494 --> 16:03.928
<i>Irish</i> boyfriend?
<i>Helping</i> the homeless?

16:03.930 --> 16:06.597
Well, every family has
one black sheep.

16:06.599 --> 16:07.932
Let's move on.

16:07.934 --> 16:10.168
How did this happen?
(pacifier pops twice)

16:10.170 --> 16:12.537
Don't you take
that tone with me.

16:14.139 --> 16:15.573
A harvard man?

16:15.575 --> 16:17.108
I was warned
there'd be nausea.

16:17.110 --> 16:19.978
I don't need them.
My life is perfect.

16:22.448 --> 16:25.350
My life is perfect.

16:25.352 --> 16:28.820
49, 50.
My life is perfect!

16:28.822 --> 16:31.656
Have you seen my
canadian penny?

16:31.658 --> 16:33.191
Oh, darn it,
darn it, darn it!

16:34.994 --> 16:37.095
Everyone out!
You're all fired!

16:37.097 --> 16:39.297
Having a family is the most
meaningless experience

16:39.299 --> 16:40.865
I could imagine.

16:40.867 --> 16:41.966
Try acting.

16:41.968 --> 16:43.201
Mm...

16:43.203 --> 16:44.268
Come on, kids.

16:44.270 --> 16:45.770
I'm taking
my bathrobe.

16:45.772 --> 16:47.105
There's a dye pack
stitched in.

16:47.107 --> 16:48.272
(loud pop)

16:48.274 --> 16:50.208
Joke's on you.
I like this better.

16:50.210 --> 16:52.010
Oh, go ahead,
take your robe.

16:52.012 --> 16:53.878
But you'll never work
in single-viewer

16:53.880 --> 16:56.914
Virtual reality
family melodrama again.

16:57.883 --> 16:59.450
Did you see
the guitar lessons sign

16:59.452 --> 17:00.818
